Bernice. Act. 25. 13. 26. 30. She was the Sister both of Agrippa the younger, and of Drusilla beforementioned. Yet S Chrysost. seems to call her Agrippa's Wife, (
   〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
) and inclined to think that she also was desirous of hearing S. Paul. The great Pomp of which S. Luke speaks, hath reminded some of the Diamond on Bernice's finger, mentioned by Iuvenal. Sat. 6. There is mention of her in Tacit. Hist. l. 2. in Iosephus often, and in Gorionides. Some have taken Bernice in the Acts to be a Man's Name, which to me is matter of admiration.
